cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.THEORY. 

This paper combines functional programming with session-based communication, which suggests it could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses typing disciplines and guarantees of normalisation and progress, which could place it in cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science). Finally, the mention of "infinite data" in the title suggests a potential connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
